@NODE install "Installation"
@{u}Installation@{uu}

   Simply copy the entire UserbaseExplorer directory to Doors: or unarchive the
UserbaseExplr archive to Doors: and you have it now installed :).

To get it on to the BBS, run it as a standard door, e.g.

 Key:  Function:   Extra:   Lo acc:  Hi acc:  Filename/Name/Dest/Path:
 
 U     34          0        0        10000    Doors:UserbaseExplorer/UBE
 
   Now you have UBE installed, just run the door and play with the menu, it's
pretty straight forward. You can alter the screen that is displayed, the
filename is @{b}Main.text@{ub}, there are no other extra files.

@{u}Technical note...@{uu}

   UBE will load the entire user.data into memory for speed & efficiency, this
means you will need enough free ram to hold the size of your user.data plus
about 90k for the door. If your system runs out of memory, UBE will not even
attempt to run (for safety reasons).

@ENDNODE

@NODE use "In use"
@{u}In use@{uu}

   Once you have @{" installed " LINK install} the door, it's time to check it out,
just run it and look at the menu. Try playing with some of the functions, it's
pretty straight forward.

@ENDNODE

